div.p: The AT() directive tells the linker:

ul.li: Place section at VMA for code execution
Store in binary at LMA for bootloader loading

div.p: Without AT(), the binary would have 3GB of padding!
rep stosb fills memory from edi to edi+ecx-1 with byte value in al (0x00)
mov edi, __bss_start mov ecx, __bss_end sub ecx, edi xor eax, eax rep stosb ; Zero BSS!
